comments: Brunson (NYK) goes to, not through Holiday's (MIL) space at the end of his drive and marginal contact occurs as Holiday's (MIL) momentum is carrying him forward.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) establishes himself in Grimes's (NYK) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Holiday (MIL) and Brunson's (NYK) engage and disengage with one another off ball and marginal contact occurs as the two come together prior to the pick.
Holiday (MIL) brings his arm toward Randle's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs as Randle (NYK) dribbles the ball off his knee.
Lopez (MIL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) brings his forearm to Bruson's (NYK) front and marginal body contact occurs during his driving shot attempt.

Robinson's (NYK) arm initiates marginal contact with Holiday's (MIL) head as he simultaneously makes contact with the loose ball. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Randle (NYK) jumps somewhat towards Lopez (MIL) and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the loose ball.
Robinson (NYK) establishes himself in Allen's (MIL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Allen (MIL) brings his arm toward Barrett's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs during Barrett's (NYK) drive.
Randle (NYK) briefly grasps Lopez's (MIL) arm underneath the basket and immediately slides his hand off as they pursue the long rebound.
Robinson (NYK) places a resting hand to Connaughton's (MIL) shoulder and immediately slides his hand off as they pursue the loose ball.

Replay review of the foul called on Antetokounmpo (MIL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Antetokounmpo (MIL) initiates contact to Robinson's (NYK) wrist and the contact affects his layup attempt.
Holiday (MIL) brushes Brunson's (NYK) arm during his drive and marginal arm contact occurs during his drive.
Brunson (NYK) gathers the loose ball and the ball does not go out of bounds.
Holiday (MIL) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Brunson (NYK), which affects his driving shot attempt.
Portis (MIL) establishes himself in Grimes's (NYK) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Connaughton (MIL) legally contests Barrett's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
A timeout is correctly whistled and granted prior to Robinson (NYK) and Holiday (MIL) getting tangled up.
Brunson (NYK) and Allen (MIL) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Lopez (MIL) has his arms slightly out of frame of his body and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.

After communicating to the Replay center, crew determined that the foul called on Barrett (NYK) did not meet the criteria for a flagrant foul. Barrett (NYK) extends his arm out and initiates contact to Connaughton's (MIL) head that affects his SQBR.
Grimes (NYK) initiates contact with Holiday's (MIL) arm and affects Holiday's (MIL) SQBR.
Quickley (NYK) brings his hands toward Matthews (MIL) and marginal contact occurs as Quickley (NYK) releases away from the contact.
Grimes (NYK) engages with Allen (MIL) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Grimes (NYK) releases away to set the screen.

Matthews (MIL) moves alongside Randle's (NYK) path during his drive to the basket, and Matthews firms up with his arms in a vertical position when the marginal contact occurs during Randle's upward shooting motion.
Randle (NYK) slightly extends his forearm into Matthews' (MIL) side during the rebound but the contact that occurs is marginal.
Barrett (NYK) commits a take foul on Hill (MIL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
